
[1]affability

   AFFABIL'ITY, n. [See Affable.] The quality of being affable; readiness
   to converse; civility and courteousness, in receiving others, and in
   conversation; condescension in manners. Affability of countenance is
   that mildness of aspect, which invites to free social intercourse.
